I expected to see gnashing of teeth and a fight break out at the door.
The plane was full, he added, “passengers boarded at lightning speed.”
Frontier also does like Spirit and charges a $2 fee for a coffee, tea, soda, or fruit juice.
Frontier said passengers who have a soda or juice can take the unopened can with them, and those who have coffee can be reserved for free.
It will always distribute water for free.
US Airways briefly attempted to charge for drinks in 2008 but backtracked seven months later after passengers complained and when no other major airline had followed.
Frontier’s decision to charge hand baggage fees when passengers do not purchase their ticket directly from the airline is its latest effort to entice customers to go to its site.
