At least one group of online hacktivists claimed to be responsible for the breakdown of the NSA site by a DSD attack.
DSD attacks aim to flood a targeted site until the servers are overloaded and the site collapses.
Cyber-tactics are not very sophisticated and attacks are not intended to penetrate the internal network of the targeted system.
The once top-secret NSA, once dubbed the “No Such Agency,” has found itself in the spotlight and heavily criticized over the past few months following a wave of revelations about its vast communications surveillance programs at home and abroad — which are part of the NSA’s secret files stolen from the agency and leaked by the former consultant.
This growing controversy around the agency has sparked much speculation that tonight’s incident was the result of a targeted cyber-operation.
