77% of French people want one, for their relatives, whether it is religious (53%), or civil (24%).
Today, 73% of people who have chosen cremation want to organize a ceremony.
66% of atheists and non-believers also desire it.
The crematoriums have adapted to this evolution of society.
"For the last ten years, they have been trying to avoid the violence of waiting, without doing anything, for an hour and a half, immediately followed by the release of the ashes," observes Michaud-Nérard.
70% of establishments now offer masters of ceremonies, who proceed, in the presence of the body, to the following ritual: welcome the assembly, appoint the deceased, connect him to others, evoke him, give meaning to his death, organize the farewell.
